# 6. Better Approach (Dynamic Programming - LCS)

## Idea

Minimum operations depend on the **Longest Common Subsequence (LCS)**.

If

```text
LCS = x
```

Then

Delete

```text
len(a)-x
```

Insert

```text
len(b)-x
```

Answer

```text
(len(a)-x)+(len(b)-x)
```

---

## Algorithm

1. Compute LCS.
2. Calculate deletions.
3. Calculate insertions.

---

## Code

```python
class Solution:
    def minInsAndDel(self, a, b):
        n = len(a)
        m = len(b)

        dp = [[0]*(m+1) for _ in range(n+1)]

        for i in range(1,n+1):
            for j in range(1,m+1):

                if a[i-1]==b[j-1]:
                    dp[i][j]=1+dp[i-1][j-1]
                else:
                    dp[i][j]=max(dp[i-1][j],dp[i][j-1])

        lcs=dp[n][m]

        return (n-lcs)+(m-lcs)
```

---

## Time Complexity

```text
O(n*m)
```

---

## Space Complexity

```text
O(n*m)
```

